<h1>@HI{{to}} conditional</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li>  @Vru{{}}@EM{{@HI{{to}}}}
<li>  @Ai{{}}@EM{{@HI{{to}}}}
<li>  @Anastem{{}}@HI{{da}}@EM{{@HI{{to}}}}
<li>  @N{{}}@HI{{da}}@EM{{@HI{{to}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The @EM{{@HI{{to}}}} conditional expresses that as a result of the action in the subordinate clause,
the action in the main clause happens as an inevitable consequence. As such, the main clause cannot be one of
volition, hope invitation or request.
</p>

<p>
The subordinate clause must be non-past even if it refers to a past event or action.
</p>

